Abstraction

     * [https://github.com/orgsync/active_interaction]ActiveInteraction -
       Manage application specific business logic.
     * [https://github.com/apotonick/apotomo]Apotomo - Based on Cells,
       Apotomo gives you widgets and encapsulation, bubbling events, AJAX
       page updates, rock-solid testing and more.
     * [https://github.com/apotonick/cells]Cells - View Components for
       Rails.
     * [https://github.com/hashrocket/decent_exposure]Decent Exposure - A
       helper for creating declarative interfaces in controllers.
     * [https://github.com/ms-ati/docile]Docile - A tiny library that lets
       you map a DSL (domain specific language) to your Ruby objects in a
       snap.
     * [https://github.com/dry-rb]dry-rb - dry-rb is a collection of
       next-generation Ruby libraries, each intended to encapsulate a
       common task.
     * [https://github.com/collectiveidea/interactor]Interactor -
       Interactor provides a common interface for performing complex
       interactions in a single request.
     * [https://github.com/adomokos/light-service]Light Service - Series
       of Actions with an emphasis on simplicity.
     * [https://github.com/cypriss/mutations]Mutations - Compose your
       business logic into commands that sanitize and validate input.
     * [https://github.com/plataformatec/responders]Responders - A set of
       Rails responders to dry up your application.
     * [https://github.com/saturnflyer/surrounded]Surrounded -
       Encapsulated related objects in a single system to add behavior
       during runtime. Extensible implementation of DCI.
     * [https://github.com/apotonick/trailblazer]Trailblazer - Trailblazer
       is a thin layer on top of Rails. It gently enforces encapsulation,
       an intuitive code structure and gives you an object-oriented
       architecture.
     * [https://github.com/apneadiving/waterfall]Waterfall - A slice of
       functional programming to chain ruby services and blocks, thus
       providing a new approach to flow control.
     * [https://github.com/krisleech/wisper]wisper - A micro library
       providing Ruby objects with Publish-Subscribe capabilities.

Admin Interface

     * [http://activeadmin.info/]ActiveAdmin - A Ruby on Rails framework
       for creating elegant backends for website administration.
     * [https://github.com/activescaffold/active_scaffold]ActiveScaffold -
       ActiveScaffold provides quick and powerful user interfaces for CRUD
       (create, read, update, delete) operations for Rails applications.
       It's excellent for generating admin interfaces, managing Data-Heavy
       Applications, creating Widgets or for quick prototyping.
       ActiveScaffold is completly customizable and offers a bunch of
       additonal features including searching, pagination, layout control
       and overrides of fields, forms and templates.
     * [https://github.com/thoughtbot/administrate]Administrate - A Rails
       engine that helps you put together a super-flexible admin
       dashboard, by Thoughtbot.
     * [http://antpaw.github.io/bhf/]bhf - A simple to use
       Rails-Engine-Gem that offers an admin interface for trusted user.
     * [http://faalis.io/]Faalis - A Rails engine which provides a robust
       platform to develop web applications. It contains a very simple yet
       powerful admin/dashboard interface too.
     * [https://github.com/sferik/rails_admin]RailsAdmin - A Rails engine
       that provides an easy-to-use interface for managing your data.
     * [https://github.com/typus/typus]Typus - Ruby on Rails control panel
       to allow trusted users edit structured content.

Analytics

     * [https://github.com/ankane/ahoy]Ahoy - A solid foundation to track
       visits and events in Ruby, JavaScript, and native apps.
     * [https://github.com/jkrall/analytical]Analytical - Gem for managing
       multiple analytics services in your rails app.
     * [https://github.com/hybridgroup/gabba]Gabba - Simple way to send
       server-side notifications to Google Analytics.
     * [https://github.com/charlotte-ruby/impressionist]Impressionist -
       Rails Plugin that tracks impressions and page views.
     * [https://github.com/tpitale/legato]Legato - Model analytics reports
       and queries against the official Google Analytics Reporting API.
     * [https://github.com/railslove/rack-tracker]Rack::Tracker - Rack
       middleware that can be hooked up to multiple services and exposing
       them in a unified fashion.
     * [https://github.com/tpitale/staccato]Staccato - Track analytics
       into the official Google Analytics Collection API.

API Builder and Discovery

     * [https://github.com/rails-api/active_model_serializers]ActiveModel:
       :Serializers - JSON serialization of objects.
     * [https://github.com/inf0rmer/blanket]Blanket - A dead simple API
       wrapper.
     * [https://github.com/crepe/crepe]Crepe - The thin API stack.
     * [http://www.ruby-grape.org/]Grape - An opinionated micro-framework
       for creating REST-like APIs in Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/remiprev/her]Her - an ORM that maps REST
       resources to Ruby objects. Designed to build applications that are
       powered by a RESTful API instead of a database.
     * [https://github.com/rails/jbuilder]jbuilder - Create JSON
       structures via a Builder-style DSL.
     * [http://jsonapi-rb.org/]jsonapi-rb - Efficient and convenient JSON
       API (de)serialization library.
     * [https://github.com/cerebris/jsonapi-resources]JSONAPI::Resources -
       JSONAPI::Resources, or "JR", provides a framework for developing a
       server that complies with the JSON API specification.
     * [https://github.com/tiagopog/jsonapi-utils]JSONAPI::Utils -
       JSONAPI::Utils is built on top of JSONAPI::Resources taking
       advantage of its resource-driven style and bringing an easy way to
       build modern JSON APIs with no or less learning curve.
     * [https://github.com/crepe/jsonite]Jsonite - A tiny, HAL-compliant
       JSON presenter for your APIs.
     * [https://github.com/interagent/pliny]Pliny - Opinionated template
       Sinatra app for writing excellent APIs in Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/nesquena/rabl]rabl - General ruby templating
       with json, bson, xml, plist and msgpack support.
     * [https://github.com/rails-api/rails-api]Rails::API - Rails for API
       only applications.
     * [https://github.com/apotonick/roar]Roar - Resource-Oriented
       Architectures in Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/balvig/spyke]Spyke - Interact with REST
       services in an ActiveRecord-like manner.
     * [https://github.com/bwillis/versioncake]Version Cake - An
       unobtrusive way to version APIs in your Rails app.
     * [https://github.com/bploetz/versionist]versionist - A plugin for
       versioning Rails based RESTful APIs.

Assets

     * [https://github.com/AssetSync/asset_sync]Asset Sync - Synchronises
       Assets between Rails and S3.
     * [https://github.com/ai/autoprefixer-rails]Autoprefixer - Parse CSS
       and add vendor prefixes to rules by Can I Use.
     * [https://github.com/thoughtbot/bourbon]Bourbon - A Lightweight Sass
       Tool Set.
     * [https://github.com/rharriso/bower-rails]bower-rails - Bower
       support for Rails projects.
     * [https://github.com/wpeterson/emoji]Emoji - Exposes the Phantom
       Open Emoji library unicode/image assets and APIs for working with
       them.
     * [https://github.com/metaskills/less-rails]Less Rails - The dynamic
       stylesheet language for the Rails asset pipeline.
     * [https://github.com/cowboyd/less.rb]Less - Leaner CSS, in your
       browser or Ruby.
     * [https://rails-assets.org/]Rails Assets - Bundler to Bower proxy.
     * [http://sass-lang.com/]Sass - Sass makes CSS fun again.
     * [https://github.com/sstephenson/sprockets]Sprockets - Rack-based
       asset packaging system.
     * [https://github.com/torba-rb/torba]Torba - Bower-less bundler for
       Sprockets.
     * [https://github.com/rails/webpacker]Webpacker - Use Webpack to
       manage app-like JavaScript modules in Rails.

Authentication and OAuth

     * [https://github.com/binarylogic/authlogic]Authlogic - Authlogic is
       a clean, simple, and unobtrusive ruby authentication solution.
     * [https://github.com/thoughtbot/clearance]Clearance - Small and
       simple email & password based authenticaton for Rails.
     * [https://github.com/plataformatec/devise]Devise - A flexible
       authentication solution for Rails based on Warden.
     * [https://github.com/jwt/ruby-jwt]JWT - JSON Web Token
       implementation in Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/nsarno/knock]Knock - Seamless JWT
       authentication for Rails API.
     * [https://github.com/halogenandtoast/monban]Monban - A very simple
       and extensible user authentication library for rails.
     * [https://github.com/intridea/omniauth]OmniAuth - A library that
       standardizes multi-provider authentication utilizing Rack
       middleware.
     * [https://github.com/jeremyevans/rodauth]Rodauth - Authentication
       and account management framework for Rack applications.
     * [https://github.com/cyx/shield]Shield - Authentication protocol for
       use in your routing and model context.
     * [https://github.com/Sorcery/sorcery]Sorcery - Magical
       Authentication for Rails 4, and Rails 5.
     * [https://github.com/hassox/warden]warden - General Rack
       Authentication Framework.
     * OAuth:
          + [https://github.com/doorkeeper-gem/doorkeeper]Doorkeeper - An
            OAuth2 provider for Rails.
          + [https://github.com/intridea/oauth2]OAuth2 - A Ruby wrapper
            for the OAuth 2.0 protocol.

Authorization

     * [https://github.com/be9/acl9]acl9 - Acl9 is a role-based
       authorization system that provides a concise DSL for securing your
       Rails application.
     * [https://github.com/chaps-io/access-granted]AccessGranted -
       Multi-role and whitelist based authorization gem for Rails.
     * [https://github.com/nathanl/authority]Authority - ORM-neutral way
       to authorize actions in your Rails app.
     * [https://github.com/CanCanCommunity/cancancan]CanCanCan -
       Continuation of CanCan, an authorization Gem for Ruby on Rails.
     * [https://github.com/stffn/declarative_authorization]Declarative
       Authorization - An authorization Rails plugin using a declarative
       DSL for specifying authorization rules in one place.
     * [https://github.com/elorest/petergate]Petergate - Easy to use and
       read action and content based authorizations.
     * [https://github.com/elabs/pundit]Pundit - Minimal authorization
       through OO design and pure Ruby classes.

Automation

     * [https://github.com/danger/danger]Danger - Automate your team's
       conventions surrounding code review.
     * [https://github.com/cantino/huginn]Huginn - Huginn is a system for
       building agents that perform automated tasks for you online.

Caching

     * [https://github.com/rails/actionpack-action_caching]Action caching
       for Action Pack - Action caching for Action Pack.
     * [https://github.com/mperham/dalli]Dalli - A high performance pure
       Ruby client for accessing memcached servers.
     * [https://github.com/artsy/garner]Garner - A set of Rack middleware
       and cache helpers that implement various caching strategies.
     * [https://github.com/Shopify/identity_cache]IdentityCache - A blob
       level caching solution to plug into ActiveRecord.
     * [https://github.com/IFTTT/kashmir]Kashmir - Kashmir is a Ruby DSL
       that makes serializing and caching objects a snap.
     * [https://github.com/sorentwo/readthis]Readthis - High performance,
       pooled, ActiveSupport compliant caching with Redis.
     * [https://github.com/orslumen/record-cache]Record Cache - Cache
       Active Model Records in Rails 3.
     * [http://redis-store.org/]redis-store - Redis Store provides a full
       set of stores (Cache, I18n, Session, HTTP Cache) for modern Ruby
       frameworks like: Ruby on Rails, Sinatra, Rack, Rack::Cache and
       I18n. It supports object marshalling, timeouts, single or multiple
       nodes, and namespaces.
     * [https://github.com/hooopo/second_level_cache]Second Level Cache -
       Write-Through and Read-Through caching library for ActiveRecord 4.

Captchas and anti-spam

     * [https://github.com/markets/invisible_captcha]Invisible Captcha -
       Unobtrusive and flexible spam protection based on the honeypot
       strategy. It also provides a time-sensitive form submission.
     * [https://github.com/joshfrench/rakismet]Rakismet - Easy Akismet and
       TypePad AntiSpam integration for Rails.
     * [https://github.com/ambethia/recaptcha]reCAPTCHA - reCaptcha API
       helpers for ruby apps.
     * [https://github.com/biola/Voight-Kampff]Voight-Kampff - A Ruby gem
       that detects bots, spiders, crawlers and replicants.

CLI Builder

     * [https://github.com/mdub/clamp]Clamp - A command-line application
       framework.
     * [https://github.com/thoughtbot/cocaine]Cocaine - A small library
       for doing (command) lines.
     * [https://github.com/commander-rb/commander]Commander - The complete
       solution for Ruby command-line executables.
     * [https://github.com/davetron5000/gli]GLI - Git-Like Interface
       Command Line Parser.
     * [https://github.com/ahoward/main]Main - A class factory and DSL for
       generating command line programs real quick.
     * [https://github.com/ruby/rake]Rake - A make-like build utility for
       Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/leejarvis/slop]Slop - Simple Lightweight Option
       Parsing.
     * [http://whatisthor.com/]Thor - A toolkit for building powerful
       command-line interfaces.
     * [https://github.com/manageiq/trollop]Trollop - A commandline option
       parser for Ruby that just gets out of your way.
     * [https://github.com/peter-murach/tty]TTY - Toolbox for developing
       CLI clients.

CLI Utilities

     * [https://github.com/awesome-print/awesome_print]Awesome Print -
       Pretty print your Ruby objects with style -- in full color and with
       proper indentation
     * [https://github.com/pickhardt/betty]Betty - Friendly English-like
       interface for your command line. Don't remember a command? Ask
       Betty.
     * [https://github.com/athityakumar/colorls]colorls - Beautifies the
       ls command, with color and font-awesome icons.
     * [https://github.com/geemus/formatador]formatador - STDOUT text
       formatting.
     * [https://github.com/janlelis/paint]Paint - Simple and fast way to
       set ANSI terminal colors.
     * [https://github.com/peter-murach/pastel]Pastel - Terminal output
       styling with intuitive and clean API.
     * [https://github.com/tombenner/ru]Ru - Ruby in your shell.
     * [https://github.com/jfelchner/ruby-progressbar]Ruby/Progressbar -
       The most flexible text progress bar library for Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/arches/table_print]TablePrint - Slice your data
       from multiple DB tables into a single CLI view.
     * [https://github.com/tj/terminal-table]Terminal Table - Ruby ASCII
       Table Generator, simple and feature rich.
     * [https://github.com/tmuxinator/tmuxinator]Tmuxinator - Create and
       manage complex tmux sessions easily.

Cloud

     * [https://github.com/aws/aws-sdk-ruby]AWS SDK for Ruby - The
       official AWS SDK for Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/projecthydra/browse-everything]browse-everythin
       g - Multi-provider Rails engine providing access to files in cloud
       storage.
     * [https://github.com/fog/fog]Fog - The Ruby cloud services library.

CMS

     * [http://alchemy-cms.com/]Alchemy CMS - A powerful, userfriendly and
       flexible Open Source Rails CMS.
     * [http://camaleon.tuzitio.com/]Camaleon CMS - A dynamic and advanced
       content management system based on Ruby on Rails 4.
     * [https://github.com/comfy/comfortable-mexican-sofa]ComfortableMexic
       anSofa - Powerful Rails 5.2+ CMS Engine.
     * [https://github.com/wearefine/fae]Fae - Flexible, open source,
       Rails CMS engine.
     * [http://www.locomotivecms.com/]LocomotiveCMS - A simple but
       powerful CMS based on Liquid templates and Mongodb database.
     * [https://github.com/publify/publify]Publify - A self hosted Web
       publishing platform on Rails.
     * [http://www.pushtype.org/]PushType - A next generation, open source
       content management system for Ruby on Rails.
     * [http://radiantcms.org/]Radiant - A no-fluff, open source content
       management system designed for small teams.
     * [http://refinerycms.com/]Refinery CMS - An open source Ruby on
       Rails content management system for Rails 3 and 4.
     * [http://www.spinacms.com/]Spina CMS - A beautiful CMS for Rails
       developers.
     * [https://github.com/CultivateLabs/storytime]Storytime - Rails 4+
       CMS and bloging engine, with a core focus on content.

Code Analysis and Metrics

     * [https://github.com/ooyala/barkeep]Barkeep - Barkeep is a fast, fun
       way to review code. Engineering organizations can use it to keep
       the bar high.
     * [https://github.com/presidentbeef/brakeman]Brakeman - A static
       analysis security vulnerability scanner for Ruby on Rails
       applications.
     * [https://github.com/square/cane]Cane - Code quality threshold
       checking as part of your build.
     * [https://github.com/danmayer/coverband]Coverband - Rack middleware
       to help measure production code coverage.
     * [https://github.com/DamirSvrtan/fasterer]Fasterer - Make your
       Rubies go faster with this command line tool highly inspired by
       fast-ruby and Sferik's talk at Baruco Conf.
     * [https://github.com/seattlerb/flay]Flay - Flay analyzes code for
       structural similarities. Differences in literal values, variable,
       class, method names, whitespace, programming style, braces vs
       do/end, etc are all ignored. Making this totally rad.
     * [https://github.com/seattlerb/flog]Flog - Flog reports the most
       tortured code in an easy to read pain report. The higher the score,
       the more pain the code is in.
     * [https://gitlab.com/coraline/fukuzatsu/tree/master]fukuzatsu -
       Complexity analysis tool with a rich web front-end.
     * [https://github.com/metricfu/metric_fu]MetricFu - A fist full of
       code metrics.
     * [https://github.com/tcopeland/pippi]Pippi - A utility for finding
       suboptimal Ruby class API usage, focused on runtime analysis.
     * [https://github.com/mmozuras/pronto]Pronto - Quick automated code
       review of your changes.
     * [https://github.com/railsbp/rails_best_practices]rails_best_practic
       es - A code metric tool for rails projects.
     * [https://github.com/troessner/reek]Reek - Code smell detector for
       Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/bbatsov/rubocop]RuboCop - A static code
       analyzer, based on the community Ruby style guide.
     * [https://github.com/whitesmith/rubycritic]Rubycritic - A Ruby code
       quality reporter.
     * [https://github.com/github/scientist]Scientist - A Ruby library for
       carefully refactoring critical paths.
     * [https://github.com/colszowka/simplecov]SimpleCov - Code coverage
       for Ruby 1.9+ with a powerful configuration library and automatic
       merging of coverage across test suites.
     * [https://github.com/amatsuda/traceroute]Traceroute - A Rake task
       gem that helps you find the dead routes and actions for your Rails
       3+ app

