Concurrency and Parallelism

     * [http://celluloid.io/]Celluloid - Actor-based concurrent object
       framework for Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/ruby-concurrency/concurrent-ruby]Concurrent
       Ruby - Modern concurrency tools including agents, futures,
       promises, thread pools, supervisors, and more. Inspired by Erlang,
       Clojure, Scala, Go, Java, JavaScript, and classic concurrency
       patterns.
     * [https://github.com/eventmachine/eventmachine]EventMachine - An
       event-driven I/O and lightweight concurrency library for Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/ahoward/forkoff]forkoff - brain-dead simple
       parallel processing for ruby.
     * [https://github.com/grosser/parallel]Parallel - Run any code in
       parallel Processes (> use all CPUs) or Threads (> speedup blocking
       operations). Best suited for map-reduce or e.g. parallel
       downloads/uploads.

