Core Extensions

     * [https://github.com/rails/rails/tree/master/activesupport]ActiveSup
       port - A collection of utility classes and standard library
       extensions.
     * [https://github.com/sporkmonger/addressable]Addressable -
       Addressable is a replacement for the URI implementation that is
       part of Ruby's standard library. It more closely conforms to RFC
       3986, RFC 3987, and RFC 6570 (level 4), providing support for IRIs
       and URI templates.
     * [https://github.com/forgecrafted/finishing_moves]Finishing Moves -
       Small, focused, incredibly useful methods added to core Ruby
       classes. Includes the endlessly useful nil_chain.
     * [https://github.com/hamstergem/hamster]Hamster - Efficient,
       immutable, and thread-safe collection classes for Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/hanami/utils]Hanami::Utils - Lightweight,
       non-monkey-patch class utilities for Hanami and Ruby app.
     * [https://github.com/rubyworks/facets]Ruby Facets - The premiere
       collection of general purpose method extensions and standard
       additions for Ruby.
     * Attributes
          + [https://github.com/cgriego/active_attr]ActiveAttr - What
            ActiveModel left out.
          + [https://github.com/applift/fast_attributes]FastAttributes -
            FastAttributes adds attributes with their types to the class.
          + [https://github.com/solnic/virtus]Virtus - Attributes on
            Steroids for Plain Old Ruby Objects.
     * Hash
          + [https://github.com/intridea/hashie]Hashie - A collection of
            tools that extend Hashes and make them more useful.

