ORM/ODM Extensions

     * Auditing and Versioning
          + [https://github.com/ActsAsParanoid/acts_as_paranoid]ActsAsPara
            noid - ActiveRecord plugin allowing you to hide and restore
            records without actually deleting them.
          + [https://github.com/collectiveidea/audited]Audited - Audited
            is an ORM extension for ActiveRecord & MongoMapper that logs
            all changes to your models.
          + [https://github.com/dockyard/ruby-destroyed_at]Destroyed At -
            Allows you to "destroy" an object without deleting the record
            or associated records.
          + [https://github.com/continuum/espinita]Espinita - Audit
            activerecord models like a boss.
          + [https://github.com/basecamp/marginalia]marginalia - Attach
            comments to your ActiveRecord queries. By default, it adds the
            application, controller, and action names as a comment at the
            end of each query.
          + [https://github.com/aq1018/mongoid-history]mongoid-history -
            Multi-user non-linear history tracking, auditing, undo, redo
            for mongoid.
          + [https://github.com/airblade/paper_trail]PaperTrail - Track
            changes to your ActiveRecord models' data for auditing or
            versioning.
          + [https://github.com/radar/paranoia]Paranoia - A
            re-implementation of acts_as_paranoid for Rails 3 and 4, using
            much, much, much less code.
          + [https://github.com/JackDanger/permanent_records]PermenantReco
            rds - Soft-delete your ActiveRecord records, like an explicit
            version of ActsAsParanoid.
     * Import
          + [https://github.com/continuum/active_importer]ActiveImporter -
            Define importers that load tabular data from spreadsheets or
            CSV files into any ActiveRecord-like ORM.
          + [https://github.com/zdennis/activerecord-import]ActiveRecord
            Import - a library for bulk inserting data using ActiveRecord.
          + [https://github.com/jamis/bulk_insert]bulk_insert - A little
            ActiveRecord extension for helping to insert lots of rows in a
            single insert statement.
          + [https://github.com/seamusabshere/data_miner]data_miner -
            Download, pull out of a ZIP/TAR/GZ/BZ2 archive, parse,
            correct, and import XLS, ODS, XML, CSV, HTML, etc. into your
            ActiveRecord models.
          + [https://github.com/cmu-is-projects/ferry]ferry - A ruby gem
            for easy data transfer.
     * Misc
          + [https://github.com/drecom/activerecord-turntable]ActiveRecord
            ::Turntable - A database sharding extension for ActiveRecord.
          + [https://github.com/franckverrot/activevalidators]ActiveValida
            tors - An exhaustive collection of off-the-shelf and tested
            ActiveModel/ActiveRecord validations.
          + [https://github.com/brainspec/enumerize]Enumerize - Enumerated
            attributes with I18n and ActiveRecord/Mongoid/MongoMapper
            support.
          + [https://github.com/salsify/goldiloader]Goldiloader -
            Automatic ActiveRecord eager loading.
          + [https://github.com/DAddYE/mini_record]mini_record -
            ActiveRecord meets DataMapper, with MiniRecord you are be able
            to write schema inside your models.
     * Multi-tenancy
          + [https://github.com/ErwinM/acts_as_tenant]Acts As Tennant -
            Add multi-tenancy to a Rails app through a shared database
            strategy.
          + [https://github.com/influitive/apartment]Apartment -
            Multi-tenancy for Rails and ActiveRecord.
          + [https://github.com/jekuno/milia]Milia - Non-invasive
            multi-tenancy for Rails which supports Devise authentication
            out of the box.
     * Social
          + [https://github.com/jackdempsey/acts_as_commentable]Acts As
            Commentable - Provides a single Comment model that can be
            attached to any model(s) within your app.
          + [https://github.com/elight/acts_as_commentable_with_threading]
            Acts As Commentable with Threading - Similar to
            acts_as_commentable; however, utilizes awesome_nested_set to
            provide threaded comments.
          + [https://github.com/tcocca/acts_as_follower]acts_as_follower -
            Allow any ActiveRecord model to follow any other model.
          + [https://github.com/twitter/activerecord-reputation-system]Act
            iveRecord Reputation System - An Active Record Reputation
            System for Rails.
          + [https://github.com/mbleigh/acts-as-taggable-on]ActsAsTaggable
            On - A tagging plugin for ActiveRecord that allows for custom
            tagging along dynamic contexts.
          + [https://github.com/ryanto/acts_as_votable]Acts As Votable -
            Allow any ActiveRecord model to be voted on, like/dislike,
            upvote/downvote, etc.
          + [https://github.com/merit-gem/merit]Merit - Adds reputation
            behavior to Rails apps in the form of Badges, Points, and
            Rankings for ActiveRecord or Mongoid.
          + [https://github.com/chaps-io/public_activity]PublicActivity -
            Provides easy activity tracking for your ActiveRecord, Mongoid
            3 and MongoMapper models in Rails 3 and 4. Similar to Github's
            Public Activity.
          + [https://github.com/kigster/simple-feed]Simple Feed - Fast and
            highly scalable read-optimized social activity feed library in
            pure Ruby, backed by Redis.
          + [https://github.com/ledermann/unread]Unread - Manage
            read/unread status of ActiveRecord objects - and it's fast.
     * Sorting
          + [https://github.com/swanandp/acts_as_list]ActsAsList -
            Provides the capabilities for sorting and reordering a number
            of objects in a list.
          + [https://github.com/mixonic/ranked-model]ranked-model - A
            modern row sorting library for ActiveRecord. It uses ARel
            aggressively and is better optimized than most other
            libraries.
     * Tree
          + [https://github.com/amerine/acts_as_tree]ActsAsTree - Extends
            ActiveRecord to add simple support for organizing items into
            parent-children relationships.
          + [https://github.com/stefankroes/ancestry]Ancestry - Organise
            ActiveRecord model into a tree structure using a variation on
            the materialised path pattern.
          + [https://github.com/collectiveidea/awesome_nested_set]Awesome
            Nested Set - Awesome Nested Set is an implementation of the
            nested set pattern for ActiveRecord models.
          + [https://github.com/mceachen/closure_tree]Closure Tree -
            Easily and efficiently make your ActiveRecord models support
            hierarchies using a Closure Table.
          + [https://github.com/benedikt/mongoid-tree]Mongoid Tree - A
            tree structure for Mongoid documents using the materialized
            path pattern.

