            aren't fun. Machinist is.
     * Mock
          + [https://github.com/zeisler/active_mocker]ActiveMocker -
            Generate mocks from ActiveRecord models for unit tests that
            run fast because they don't need to load Rails or a database.
          + [https://github.com/iridakos/duckrails]DuckRails - Tool for
            mocking API endpoints quickly & dynamically.
          + [https://github.com/alovak/test_xml]TestXml - TestXml is a
            small extension for testing XML/HTML.
          + [https://github.com/bblimke/webmock]WebMock - Library for
            stubbing and setting expectations on HTTP requests.
     * WebDrivers
          + [https://github.com/SeleniumHQ/selenium/tree/master/rb]Seleniu
            m WebDriver - Ruby bindings for WebDriver.
          + [https://github.com/fredwu/api_taster]API Taster - A quick and
            easy way to visually test your Rails application's API.
          + [https://github.com/teampoltergeist/poltergeist]Poltergeist -
            A PhantomJS driver for Capybara.
          + [https://github.com/watir/watir/]Watir - Web application
            testing in Ruby.
     * Extra
          + [https://github.com/thoughtbot/appraisal]Appraisal - Appraisal
            integrates with bundler and rake to test your library against
            different versions of dependencies.
          + [https://github.com/ArturT/knapsack]Knapsack - Optimal test
            suite parallelisation across CI nodes for RSpec, Cucumber,
            Minitest, Spinach and Turnip.
          + [https://github.com/mbj/mutant]mutant - Mutant is a mutation
            testing tool for Ruby.
          + [https://github.com/grosser/parallel_tests]Parallel Tests -
            Speedup Test::Unit + RSpec + Cucumber by running parallel on
            multiple CPUs (or cores).
          + [https://github.com/k-tsj/power_assert]power_assert - Power
            Assert for Ruby.
          + [https://github.com/flood-io/ruby-jmeter]Ruby-JMeter - A Ruby
            based DSL for building JMeter test plans.
          + [https://github.com/rails/spring]Spring - Preloads your rails
            environment in the background for faster testing and Rake
            tasks.
          + [https://github.com/travisjeffery/timecop]timecop - Provides
            "time travel" and "time freezing" capabilities, making it dead
            simple to test time-dependent code.
          + [https://github.com/vcr/vcr]vcr - Record your test suite's
            HTTP interactions and replay them during future test runs for
            fast, deterministic, accurate tests.
          + [https://github.com/Nedomas/zapata]Zapata - Who has time to
            write tests? This is a revolutionary tool to make them write
            themselves.

Third-party APIs

     * [https://github.com/futuresimple/dropbox-api]Dropbox - Dropbox API
       Ruby Client.
     * [https://github.com/huydx/facy]facy - Command line power tool for
       facebook.
     * [https://github.com/nov/fb_graph2]fb_graph2 - A full-stack Facebook
       Graph API wrapper.
     * [https://github.com/RaVbaker/flickr]flickr - A Ruby interface to
       the Flickr API.
     * [https://github.com/NARKOZ/gitlab]gitlab - Ruby wrapper and CLI for
       the GitLab API.
     * [https://github.com/googleads/google-api-ads-ruby]google-api-ads-ru
       by - Google Adwords Ruby client
     * [https://github.com/gmailgem/gmail]gmail - A Rubyesque interface to
       Gmail, with all the tools you'll need.
     * [https://github.com/hipchat/hipchat-rb]hipchat-rb - HipChat HTTP
       API Wrapper in Ruby with Capistrano hooks.
     * [https://github.com/Instagram/instagram-ruby-gem]instagram-ruby-gem
       - The official gem for the Instagram REST and Search APIs.
     * [https://github.com/sshaw/itunes_store_transporter]itunes_store_tra
       nsporter - Ruby wrapper around Apple's iTMSTransporter program.
     * [https://github.com/hexgnu/linkedin]linkedin - Provides an
       easy-to-use wrapper for LinkedIn's REST APIs.
     * [http://octokit.github.io/octokit.rb]Octokit - Ruby toolkit for the
       GitHub API.
     * [https://github.com/pusher/pusher-http-ruby]Pusher - Ruby server
       library for the Pusher API.
     * [https://github.com/ejholmes/restforce]Restforce - A Ruby client
       for the Salesforce REST api.
     * [https://github.com/dcparker/ruby-gmail]ruby-gmail - A Rubyesque
       interface to Gmail.
     * [https://github.com/jeremytregunna/ruby-trello]ruby-trello -
       Implementation of the Trello API for Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/kciter/simple-slack-bot]simple-slack-bot - You
       can easily make Slack Bot.
     * [https://github.com/stevenosloan/slack-notifier]Slack Notifier - A
       simple wrapper for posting to Slack channels.
     * [https://github.com/aki017/slack-ruby-gem]Slack ruby gem - A Ruby
       wrapper for the Slack API.
     * [https://github.com/soundcloud/soundcloud-ruby]soundcloud-ruby -
       Official SoundCloud API Wrapper for Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/sferik/t]t - A command-line power tool for
       Twitter.
     * [https://github.com/keepcosmos/terjira]terjira - A command-line
       power tool for Jira.
     * [https://github.com/tweetstream/tweetstream]tweetstream - A simple
       library for consuming Twitter's Streaming API.
     * [https://github.com/twilio/twilio-ruby]twilio-ruby - A module for
       using the Twilio REST API and generating valid TwiML.
     * [https://github.com/sferik/twitter]twitter - A Ruby interface to
       the Twitter API.
     * [https://github.com/kenpratt/wikipedia-client]wikipedia - Ruby
       client for the Wikipedia API.
     * [https://github.com/Fullscreen/yt]Yt - An object-oriented Ruby
       client for YouTube API V3.

Video

     * [https://github.com/streamio/streamio-ffmpeg]Streamio FFMPEG -
       Simple yet powerful wrapper around the ffmpeg command for reading
       metadata and transcoding movies.
     * [https://github.com/donmelton/video_transcoding]Video Transcoding -
       Tools to transcode, inspect and convert videos.

View helpers

     * [https://github.com/dejan/auto_html]auto_html - Rails extension for
       transforming URLs to appropriate resource (image, link, YouTube,
       Vimeo video...).
     * [https://github.com/fullscreen/bh]Bh - Bootstrap Helpers for Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/gazay/gon]gon - If you need to send some data
       to your js files and you don't want to do this with long way
       through views and parsing - use gon.
     * [https://github.com/peresleguine/pluggable_js]PluggableJs -
       Page-specific javascript for Rails applications with the ability of
       passing data from a controller.

Web Crawling

     * [https://github.com/chriskite/anemone]anemone - Ruby library and
       CLI for crawling websites.
     * [https://github.com/gottfrois/link_thumbnailer]LinkThumbnailer -
       Ruby gem that generates thumbnail images and videos from a given
       URL. Much like popular social website with link preview.
     * [https://github.com/sparklemotion/mechanize]Mechanize - Mechanize
       is a ruby library that makes automated web interaction easy.
     * [https://github.com/jaimeiniesta/metainspector]MetaInspector - Ruby
       gem for web scraping purposes.
     * [https://github.com/propublica/upton]Upton - A batteries-included
       framework for easy web-scraping.
     * [https://github.com/felipecsl/wombat]Wombat - Web scraper with an
       elegant DSL that parses structured data from web pages.

Web Frameworks

     * [https://github.com/camping/camping]Camping - A web microframework
       which consistently stays at less than 4kB of code.
     * [http://cuba.is/]Cuba - A microframework for web development.
     * [https://github.com/patriciomacadden/hobbit]Hobbit - A minimalistic
       microframework built on top of Rack.
     * [http://hanamirb.org/]Hanami - It aims to bring back Object
       Oriented Programming to web development, leveraging on a stable
       API, a minimal DSL, and plain objects.
     * [http://ruby-hyperloop.org/]Hyperloop - A Complete Isomorphic Ruby
       Framework using React, Rails and Opal
     * [http://www.padrinorb.com/]Padrino - A full-stack ruby framework
       built upon Sinatra.
     * [https://www.pakyow.org/]Pakyow - A framework for building modern
       web-apps in Ruby. It helps you build working software faster with a
       development process that remains friendly to both designers and
       developers.
     * [https://github.com/rack-app/rack-app]Rack::App - Bare bone
       minimalistic framework for building rack apps.
     * [http://ramaze.net/]Ramaze - A simple, light and modular
       open-source web application framework written in Ruby.
     * [http://roda.jeremyevans.net/]Roda - A routing tree web framework.
     * [http://rubyonrails.org/]Ruby on Rails - A web-application
       framework that includes everything needed to create database-backed
       web applications according to the Model-View-Controller (MVC)
       pattern.
     * [http://scorchedrb.com/]Scorched - Light-weight, inheritable and
       composable web framework, inspired by Sinatra.
     * [http://www.sinatrarb.com/]Sinatra - Classy web-development dressed
       in a DSL.
     * [https://github.com/soveran/syro/]Syro - Simple router for web
       applications.
     * [https://github.com/voltrb/volt]Volt - A Ruby web framework where
       your ruby code runs on both the server and the client.

Web Servers

     * [https://github.com/postrank-labs/goliath]Goliath - A non-blocking
       Ruby web server framework.
     * [https://github.com/boazsegev/iodine]Iodine - An non-blocking HTTP
       and Websocket web server optimized for Linux/BDS/macOS and Ruby
       MRI.
     * [https://www.phusionpassenger.com/]Phusion Passenger - Fast and
       robust web server and application server.
     * [https://github.com/puma/puma]Puma - A modern, concurrent web
       server for Ruby.
     * [http://rack.github.io/]Rack - A common Ruby web server interface.
       By itself, it's just a specification and utility library, but all
       Ruby web servers implement this interface.
     * [https://github.com/celluloid/reel]Reel - Celluloid::IO-powered web
       server.
     * [http://code.macournoyer.com/thin]Thin - Tiny, fast & funny HTTP
       server.
     * [https://github.com/torquebox/torquebox]TorqueBox - A Ruby
       application server built on JBoss AS7 and JRuby.
     * [http://unicorn.bogomips.org/]Unicorn - Rack HTTP server for fast
       clients and Unix.

WebSocket

     * [http://anycable.io/]AnyCable - Polyglot replacement for Ruby
       WebSocket servers with Action Cable protocol.
     * [http://faye.jcoglan.com/ruby.html]Faye - A set of tools for simple
       publish-subscribe messaging between web clients.
     * [https://github.com/firehoseio/firehose]Firehose - Build realtime
       Ruby web applications.
     * [https://github.com/stevegraham/slanger]Slanger - Open Pusher
       implementation compatible with Pusher libraries.
     * [https://github.com/chrismccord/render_sync]RenderSync - Real-time
       Rails Partials.
     * [https://github.com/websocket-rails/websocket-rails]Websocket-Rails
       - Creates a built in WebSocket server inside a Rails application
       with ease, and also support streaming HTTP.

Services and Apps

   Online tools, services and APIs to simplify development.
     * [https://appsignal.com/]AppSignal - Better monitoring for your
       Rails applications.
     * [https://www.codacy.com/]Codacy - Automated Code Review for Ruby,
       Rails, JS, PHP, Python etc. Security, Coverage & Quality.
     * [https://codeclimate.com/]CodeClimate - Quality & security analysis
       for Ruby on Rails and Javascript.
     * [https://www.deppbot.com/]deppbot - Automated Security and
       Dependency Updates.
     * [https://gemnasium.com/]Gemnasium - Monitor your project
       dependencies and alert you about updates and security
       vulnerabilities.
     * [https://github.com/]GitHub - Powerful collaboration, code review,
       and code management for open source and private projects.
     * [https://about.gitlab.com/gitlab-ci/]Gitlab CI - Integrate with
       your GitLab to run tests for your projects.
     * [https://about.gitlab.com/]GitLab - Open source software to
       collaborate on code.
     * [https://hakiri.io/]Hakiri - Ship Secure Ruby Apps.
     * [https://houndci.com/]HoundCI - Review your Ruby code for style
       guide violations.
     * [https://huboard.com/]HuBoard - Kanban board for GitHub issues.
     * [http://inch-ci.org/]Inch CI - Documentation badges for Ruby
       projects.
     * [https://github.com/nanobox-io/nanobox]Nanobox - A micro-PaaS
       (PaaS) for creating consistent, isolated, Ruby environments
       deployable anywhere [https://nanobox.io/]https://nanobox.io.
     * [https://github.com/OctoLinker/browser-extension]OctoLinker -
       Navigate through projects on GitHub.com efficiently with the
       OctoLinker browser extension.
     * [https://semaphoreapp.com/]SemaphoreCI - Hosted continuous
       integration and deployment service for open source and private
       projects.
     * [https://www.sideci.com/]SideCI - Automated Code Review with GitHub
       PR. - Monitoring Style Violations, Quality, Security, Dependencies.
     * [https://travis-ci.com/]Travis CI.com - Take care of running your
       tests and deploying your private apps.
     * [https://travis-ci.org/]Travis CI.org - A distributed build system
       for the open source community.
     * [https://vexor.io/]Vexor CI - A distributed cloud web-service for
       building and testing software, a continuous integration tool for
       private apps with pay-per-minute billing model.

Resources

   Where to discover new Ruby libraries, projects and trends.
     * [https://ruby.libhunt.com/]Awesome Ruby @LibHunt - Your go-to Ruby
       Toolbox. The Awesome Ruby collection + ordering by popularity,
       additional metadata and comparisons.
     * [https://github.com/trending?l=ruby]GitHub Trending - Find what
       repositories the GitHub community is most excited about today.
     * [http://greenruby.org/]Green Ruby News - A feed of fresh links of
       the week about ruby, javascript, webdev and devops.
     * [http://www.opensourcerails.com/]Open Source Rails - A gallery of
       the best open source rack and Ruby on Rails web applications.
     * [https://github.com/dreikanter/ruby-bookmarks]Ruby Bookmarks - Ruby
       and Ruby on Rails bookmarks collection.
     * [http://rubydaily.org/]RubyDaily - Community driven news.
     * [http://www.rubyflow.com/]RubyFlow - Ruby Programming Community
       Link Blog.
     * [http://rubyland.news/]Ruby Land - A well maintained Ruby/Rails
       aggregator that contains news, opinions, tutorials, and more.
     * [http://devchat.tv/ruby-rogues]Ruby Rogues - Weekly panel
       discussion about programming, primarily in Ruby.
     * [http://rubyweekly.com/]Ruby Weekly - A free, once-weekly e-mail
       round-up of Ruby news and articles.
     * [https://www.ruby-toolbox.com/]The Ruby Toolbox - A comprehensive
       catalog of Ruby and Rails plug-ins, gems, tools and resources for
       Ruby developers with popularity ratings based on GitHub watchers
       and Gem downloads.

